				<li id="16719958" class="cmnt-root" data="2" data-d="1655776019000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578865/Blue-Dancer-Charm" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">20 Jun 2022 21:46</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16719958" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">DS3 required one to wear armor in each slot to &quot;activate&quot; defense from attributes; that is no longer the case in ER, you can be completely naked and still have full defense.<br/><br/>So, you can wear no armor to maximize benefit from the blue dancer charm, and then use a combination of Dragon Greatshield Talisman, Boiled Crab, or Black Flame&apos;s Protection for upwards of 36% physical negation. Not shabby, but is PvE only (DGST&apos;s effect is quartered in PvP).<br/><br/>As someone who enjoyed a Flynn&apos;s Ring build in DS3 PvP, there&apos;s much more going for the dancer charm now, but also a lot working against it. Having no negation in PvP opens you up to a lot of one-shot deaths from ashes of war. And the bonus damage is not really worth the trade. It&apos;s pretty seldom the difference between killing someone in 2 hits rather than 3.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16719958" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16719958" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><s