				<li id="16628217" class="cmnt-root" data="38" data-d="1650283559000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578865/Blue-Dancer-Charm" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">18 Apr 2022 08:05</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16628217" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Effect of this talisman is simple.<br/><br/>1) It only affects physical damage. The damage bonus increases in inverse proportion to the weight of your equipment. The damage bonus has soft caps at 8, 16 and 20 equip load. Once equip load is 30 or higher the talisman has no effect.<br/><br/>2) It doesn&apos;t matter whether the weapon is heavy or light. I think one guy made a mistake and he messed up this wiki page. Requires correction.<br/><br/>3) It also affects the entire physical AR. Not only scaling but also base damage. Holy crabby I don&apos;t know how low the IQ must be to think of it that way, but anyway, someone misunderstood this and wrote the wrong wiki page. Requires correction.<br/><br/>4) Weapon upgrade level doesn&apos;t matter. Requires correction.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16628217" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16628217" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</