				<li id="16534760" class="cmnt-root" data="89" data-d="1647641333000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><a class="comment-username" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=119099" rel="nofollow"  target="_blank" style="color: #;">yoduh</a></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578865/Blue-Dancer-Charm" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">18 Mar 2022 18:08</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16534760" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">this shit is weird.  first the facts: the talisman gives a bonus to <b>physical scaling damage only</b>, i.e. when a weapon says its damage is &quot;physical: 100 +50&quot;, equipping this talisman will increase the damage to something like &quot;100 +75&quot;.  from testing a few different weapons I&apos;ve found out a few things:<br/><br/>1) the lighter the weapon weight, the higher the bonus.  I don&apos;t mean equip load either, I mean just the weapon weight itself.  Equip load being at 5, a dagger weighing 1.5 will receive almost 50% bonus to scaling damage, whereas a greatsword weighing 23 will receive about a 33% bonus.  now you&apos;re probably asking yourself how can equip load still be 5 for both weapons?  the trick is if your current equip load is 5 while wearing the talisman, and then you hover (DONT equip) a weapon, the +scaling damage bonus from the talisman is calculated using your CURRENT equip load.  the number you&apos;re seeing is as if the weapon was equipped <b>but your equip load stayed the same</b>.  as soon as you equip the weapon the +scaling damage recalculates.<br/><br/>what this really means is if you&apos;re just browsing your equipment, just viewing the stats without equipping, then the scaling bonus is showing higher than it should be for weapons that would increase your equipment load, and lower than it should be for weapons that decrease your equipment load. You can only really know the true value by actually equipping the weapon!<br/><br/>2) your weapon upgrade level affects the bonus, where the WORSE your weapon currently is in terms of upgrades, the BETTER this talisman is.  I compared Ruins Greatsword +0 vs Ruins Greatsword +10, with theoretical equip load of 0.9 (naked + talisman). the +0 sword gets a +32%  scaling increase vs 25% scaling increase for the +10 sword.  This percent difference got smaller as equip load increased to around only 2% diff at high equip load.<br/><br/>3) when plotted, the talisman has soft caps at 8, 16 and 20.  The best scaling happens at 8 and below, then the bonus starts falling off until 16 where the fall off becomes worse, worse again at 20, and then there&apos;s a hardcap at 30 where you will not receive ANY bonus by having this talisman equipped.<br/><br/><br/>edit: went ahead and edited the wiki with this information.  people feel free to add or correct anything i got wrong</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16534760" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16534760" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>91</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>2</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16534760"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16534760" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16534760"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
